               <head>Būstān-i khayāl by Mīr Muḥammad Taqī Khayāl</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85132085">
                  <summary>The first (ff. 1-156) and second (ff. 158-363) 
            <term xml:lang="fa">Gulzār</term>of the second 
            <term xml:lang="fa">Gulshan</term>of the second 
            <term xml:lang="fa">Bahār</term>, or first 
            <term xml:lang="fa">Gulistān</term>, forming the the sixth and seventh volumes of Mīr Muḥammad Taqī Khayāl's Būstān-i Khāyāl (Garden of Imagination), a blend of historical and ficticious
            tales composed in fifteen volumes in India between 1742 and 1756.
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_578B-item1">
